  "decision_conditions": [
    "The submitted front garden plan by reason of its sparse quantity and quality of soft landscaping fails to justify or mitigate the retention of more than 50% hardstanding within the front garden area of the property to be considered acceptable for enhancing or preserving the character and appearance of the Hanger Hill (Haymills) Estate Conservation Area. As such, the excessive area of hardstanding would be harmful to the established character of the conservation area and its retention is contrary to policies D3, D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (2021), and policies 5.10, 7B & 7C of Ealing's Development Management DPD and the Hanger Hill (Haymills) Estate Management Plan."
